Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Healer ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	SORTKEY:Class_Healer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.HealerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality								DESC:A healer is proficient with all simple weapons. Healers are proficient with light armor.  If a healer wears metal armor she loses the use of all healer spells, supernatural abilities, and spell-like abilities for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=ArmorProfLight|TYPE=WeaponProfSimple																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:pg. 9
Spells				KEY:Healer ~ Spells					SORTKEY:Class_Healer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.HealerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality								DESC:A Healer must choose and prepare his spells in advance (see below). To prepare or cast a spell, a Healer must have a Wisdom score equal to at least 10 + the spell level. The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a Healer's spell is 10 + the spell level + the Healer's Charisma modifier. Like other spellcasters, a Healer can cast only a certain number of spells of each spell level per day. Her base daily spell allotment is given on Table: The Healer. In addition, she receives bonus spells per day if she has a high Wisdom score. Healers meditate or pray for their spells. Each healer must choose a time at which she must spend 1 hour each day in quiet contemplation or supplication to regain her daily allotment of spells. Time spent resting has no effect on whether a cleric can prepare spells. A Healer may prepare and cast any spell on the Healer spell list, provided that she can cast spells of that level, but she must choose which spells to prepare during her daily meditation.																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:pg. 9


